products.name: Rowhouse Brooch - Orange and Blue
products.description:
Lovingly nicknamed Jellybean Row, colourful row houses line the streets of downtown St Johns. Green, blue, purple, red, orange... Every colour you can imagine, sometimes matching, sometimes clashing, combined with sloping hills all come together to create a unique visual you're not likely to find anywhere else. 

These brooches are laser cut from maple plywood, about 2 inches in height. They have hand painted details and are finished with a varnish sealant with a silver c clasp brooch pin. Due to the handmade nature of this item and keeping in the spirit of Jellybean Row, each piece will be slightly different from another. 

All pieces are designed and produced by myself at my home studio in St. John's, Newfoundland.

products.name: Labrador Brooch - Natural
products.description:
The Newfoundland and Labrador Labrador Region page says it the best:

"Labrador, The Big Land, one of the last untamed, unspoiled places left on earth. It stretches from the Strait of Belle Isle in the south, to Cape Chidley in the far north, boasting towering mountains, massive rock faces and an infinite supply of lakes and rivers, not to mention waters seasonally teeming with whales and icebergs. Here, you'll find plenty of fresh air, crystal clear water and truly authentic people."

It's a place that those who call home love fiercely, and a place that visitors wish they could call home. No matter if you're a Livyer or a CFA (Come From Away), with this Labrador map brooch showcasing Labrador City, you can take a little piece of The Big Land with you wherever you go.

These brooches are laser cut from oak plywood, about 2 inches in height. They have hand painted details and are finished with a varnish sealant with a silver c clasp brooch pin. Due to the handmade nature of this item, each piece will be slightly different from another.

All pieces are designed and produced by myself at my home studio in St. John's, Newfoundland.

products.name: Newfoundland Brooch - Natural
products.description:
The Newfoundland and Labrador Tourism page says it the best:

"This is where the sun rises first. Where Vikings landed over 1,000 years ago. This place is home to the oldest settlement and the oldest city in North America, but is the youngest province of Canada. A vast land, with a relatively small population, Newfoundland and Labrador has some of the friendliest people you'll ever meet."

It's a place that those who call home love fiercely, and a place that visitors wish they could call home. No matter if you're a Livyer or a CFA (Come From Away), with this Newfoundland map brooch showcasing the capital St Johns, you can take a little piece of home with you wherever you go.

These brooches are laser cut from meranti plywood, about 2 inches in height. They have hand painted details and are finished with a varnish sealant with a silver c clasp brooch pin. Due to the handmade nature of this item, each piece will be slightly different from another.

All pieces are designed and produced by myself at my home studio in St. John's, Newfoundland.
